  Ha Do Kwon   
 So Hee Jung

6
00:00:29,180 --> 00:00:31,970
 The Witch's Diner

7
00:00:34,730 --> 00:00:37,510
 Our Yun Gi, what do you dream of becoming later on?

8
00:00:37,510 --> 00:00:38,580
 A doctor!

9
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:43,410
 I will become a doctor to heal your illness, earn lots of money,

10
00:00:43,410 --> 00:00:46,060
 listen to Mom and Dad, and grow up well.

11
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:48,860
 You really are one of a kind!

12
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:52,640
 Our son is the best!

13
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:55,060
 A doctor.

14
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:06,500
Hello, I am Bae Yun Gi, a man who wants to become a true employee of this generation.

15
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:12,230
At a young age, I wanted to become an archaeologist to find hidden treasures, so I joined the Department of History.

16
00:01:12,230 --> 00:01:18,580
I want to join Daesan Investment in their journey to find unknown treasures to invest in.

17
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:26,840
Last, I'd like to request that you tell us your appeal which would make us hire you.

18
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:31,360
While I studied at Harvard, I only thought of one thing: the Korean society.

19
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:34,520
Let us become the talent which Korea needs to stand tall.

20
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:37,950
And now, I will work hard to become the person that Daesan needs.

21
00:01:37,950 --> 00:01:40,350
If you hire me, you will not regret it.

22
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:44,760
 (In Russian)  Global investment strategy, understanding the world!

23
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:47,290
 (In Chinese)  Furthermore, for the future we have to face

24
00:01:47,290 --> 00:01:50,550
 (In Japanese)  I am ready.

25
00:01:52,660 --> 00:01:55,100
Candidate 515, what about you?

26
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:59,300
Yes... well, I'm ready to do anything, even die for you.

27
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:01,730
What do you mean? Times have changed.

28
00:02:01,730 --> 00:02:04,390
That's right... so...

29
00:02:04,390 --> 00:02:06,480
Okay, what about you, candidate 516?

30
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:11,010
I, too, will work hard in order to not disappoint you.

31
00:02:22,130 --> 00:02:24,710
Ah... their qualifications are really all...

32
00:02:25,690 --> 00:02:28,150
I could have done better,

33
00:02:28,150 --> 00:02:29,650
but suddenly my stomach...

34
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:32,390
Candidate 516 is the boss's son, right?

35
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:33,920
Yes, it's his second child.

36
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:37,040
Hey, you know, they look really similar.

37
00:02:37,890 --> 00:02:41,430
What's the point of studying so hard and developing qualifications?

38
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:43,360
Some are born with a gold spoon.

39
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,740
Well, that's how life is.

40
00:02:58,020 --> 00:03:03,020
 The Witch's Diner 
 Ep.3 Chicken and rice soup for the youth

41
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:09,570
This...

42
00:03:09,570 --> 00:03:12,220
 Ouch! That hurts, dang it!

43
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:15,120
Yesterday, when Gil Yong was here, it spoke.

44
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:18,440
 Of course. What type of mandrake doesn't talk?

45
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:21,700
It spoke because it's a mandrake?

46
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:30,860
I'm in the middle of taking a nap, so don't bother me.

47
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:32,980
Wow, it spoke again! It spoke again!

48
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:34,930
- What are you doing? 
 - What?

49
00:03:34,930 --> 00:03:37,780
Stop procrastinating and come over here.

50
00:03:41,050 --> 00:03:43,230
Here. Clean this.

51
00:03:43,230 --> 00:03:44,850
Yes.

52
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:55,500
"A newborn's first cry"...

53
00:03:56,850 --> 00:04:00,460
''The last day of a terminally ill patient''...

54
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:05,000
What is all this?

55
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,690
You can see that?

56
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:10,530
Yes.

57
00:04:10,530 --> 00:04:14,780
Are all of these things the prices of the wishes?

58
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:25,460
Someone's price can become the ingredient for someone else's wish.

59
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:36,300
Hey, what was Gil Yong's wish yesterday?

60
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,820
Are you interested in him?

61
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:41,980
What? As if! What nonsense are you saying?

62
00:04:52,690 --> 00:04:56,490
Hey Yun Gi, come have a cup of coffee.

63
00:04:56,490 --> 00:04:57,830
Thank you.

64
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,490
- Cigarette? 
 -  Oh, um...

65
00:04:59,490 --> 00:05:03,160
No... no thank you, I don't smoke.

66
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,950
- It's very hard, right? 
 - No, it's okay.

67
00:05:05,950 --> 00:05:08,410
I hear it's very hard to find a job these days.

68
00:05:08,410 --> 00:05:11,220
Shouldn't you at least take the civil servant's exam?

69
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:14,280
I still have student loans, so I can't dream of it.

70
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,190
There are school fees and textbook fees. No way...

71
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:20,220
It must be difficult. Drink, Drink!

72
00:05:21,590 --> 00:05:24,430
Ah, it must be very tiring.

