00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:29,460
Oh, hey, Mom. 
♬  looking back  ♬

91
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:35,130
♬  to see that there is no one else  ♬

92
00:07:35,130 --> 00:07:41,190
♬  wondering, if I'm behind, away it of it all  ♬

93
00:07:41,190 --> 00:07:44,430
♬  Without you  ♬

94
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:48,890
♬  I guess I've finally realized   ♬

95
00:07:48,890 --> 00:07:54,730
♬  There's nothing else I care as much as you.   ♬

96
00:07:54,730 --> 00:07:59,030
♬  As much as you.  ♬

97
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:08,560
♬  If I walk this empty road  ♬

98
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:14,990
♬  A thousand miles with you, I'll never be alone   ♬

99
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:22,530
♬  If I walk this empty road  ♬

100
00:08:22,530 --> 00:08:24,730
Welcome. What can I get you?

101
00:08:24,730 --> 00:08:28,990
♬  With you, I'll never be alone   ♬

102
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,600
Yes.

103
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:12,410
Seriously, what was that?

104
00:09:12,410 --> 00:09:15,170
I had a nightmare today as well.

105
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:19,530
- Welcome. 
 - Welcome.

106
00:09:19,530 --> 00:09:21,930
Put your hands in the air and don't move!

107
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,960
Give me everything you have!

108
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:28,200
The... th-the... cash, card! Um...

109
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:32,570
Give me everything! And uh... and give me all of your food too!

110
00:09:32,570 --> 00:09:36,240
- What? F-Food? 
 - Yeah.

111
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,710
Wh-Whatever you have.

112
00:09:38,710 --> 00:09:42,190
Here, here, here... put it all in here.

113
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:51,960
 The most unexpected events are usually inevitable.

114
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:57,160
 Only the outcome depends on the choices that you make.

115
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,600
 Oh, Mom... I'll get a job soon.

116
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,200
 What will you do if you get sicker? I said don't worry!

117
00:10:00,230 --> 00:10:03,970
 What is this? Is it this guy's memories?

118
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:10,000
- Noona, are you okay? 
 - A-Are you okay?

119
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,250
Gosh, hurry and put it in!

120
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:16,320
What are you doing? Are you planning something fishy?  Don't move!

121
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:20,340
- Can't you see she's hurt? 
 - So hurry up and put it in the bag!

122
00:10:20,340 --> 00:10:23,940
Alright! We don't have money, and...

123
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:27,440
There... That's all I have in my wallet.

124
00:10:28,830 --> 00:10:31,720
What's all this noise?

125
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:40,220
What are you doing at my store?

126
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:45,270
Are you the boss here? No, you! You! You wench!

127
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:48,300
You! You too. Give me everything you have!

128
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:51,310
The card in your wallet... and give me the card password too!

129
00:10:51,310 --> 00:10:54,510
- "You wench"?
 - Yes! Or do you want to die?

130
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:58,200
I'll stab her now!

131
00:10:59,090 --> 00:11:01,130
What if I don't want to?

132
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:03,310
Don't come! Don't come near me!

133
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:06,780
I said don't come! Why do you keep walking?

134
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:08,620
- Don't come!
 - Hey!

135
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:12,460
Hey! Why are you hitting me? I'll just—

136
00:11:20,410 --> 00:11:23,290
I'm sorry.

137
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:25,700
My mom needs money for her surgery.

138
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:29,460
I've been starving for days, so I lost perspective.

139
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:31,880
I'm very sorry.

140
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:36,280
But still, you have to work to make money. How could you resort to robbery?

141
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:41,260
I did try my best by submitting dozens of resumes every day, but...

142
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:47,560
If I lower my standards, other overqualified applicants lower their standards with me.

143
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:50,570
So I can't compete.

144
00:11:50,570 --> 00:11:55,800
I couldn't even dream of language training or improving my specs because I was paying tuition.

145
00:11:56,750 --> 00:12:00,210
It is rather hard to get a job these days, isn't it?

146
00:12:00,210 --> 00:12:02,790
Even with vacancies, they only hire people with experience.

147
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:06,650
But if you're a recent graduate, of course, you have none.

148
00:12:06,650 --> 00:12:09,310
The student loan alone is 40 million won (~40k USD).

149
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:13,920
I couldn't handle the fees for the civil service exam on top of my daily expenses. I can't get employed either.

150
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:18,110
It goes without saying that life in the world isn't easy.

151
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:23,520
Why should I be the only one who's so unhappy?

152
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:26,890
Why am I the only one who has no place in this world?

153
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:31,200
- Only you?
 - I'm sorry.

154
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,670
I don't dare ask you to be fair to me. I'm really sorry.

155
00:12:35,410 --> 00:12:37,190
Stop complaining and give me your order.

156
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:40,100
Okay... What?

157
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:43,160
This is a witch's restaurant that makes wishes come true.

158
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:46,980
M-Make an order, you say?

159
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:49,400
Wish. What's your wish?

160
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,640
I-I want a job. It may as well be in a decent place too.

161
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:57,690
When I wake up in the morning, I want there to always be a place for me to go to, for once.

162
00:12:57,690 --> 00:13:00,370
It's not even a big deal.

163
00:13:01,710 --> 00:13:04,450
- Wait a second, Ms. Witch. 
 - What?

164
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,580
It won't take long.

165
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:11,790
- You said you were Bae Yun Gi, right? 
 - Yes.

166
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:14,590
I want you to think about it one more time.

167
00:13:14,590 --> 00:13:17,640
You can't take your wish back.

168
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:19,920
So you shouldn't have any regrets about this.

169
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:23,390
You don't even know how great the cost will be.

170
00:13:23,390 --> 00:13:27,320
Whether it's big or small, that's for him to bear.

171
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:29,720
It's not like you're going to live for his sake.

172
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:33,030
- I mean, it's because I'm not going to live for him that I'm— 
 - Shut up.

173
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:36,000
I'm sorry, but what are you talking about?

174
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,130
Did I misunderstand you, or was I not supposed to understand you, or what—?

175
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:42,220
Is it okay for you if I can explain it to you a little?

176
00:13:42,220 --> 00:13:43,720
As someone who experienced this.

177
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:46,410
 Notice

178
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:49,020
So it's...

179
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:54,180
You're saying the witch is the business concept of this store, right? Oh.

180
00:13:54,180 --> 00:13:57,020
Wow, your boss is really brilliant.

181
00:13:57,020 --> 00:13:59,360
If you make a wish, it will surely come true.

182
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:01,960
But you do need to pay the price for it.

183
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:07,220
- The wish... will come true? 
 - Yes.

184
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:09,230
The price... Ah...

185
00:14:11,210 --> 00:14:14,310
Just report me to the police already. Don't make fun of me like that.

186
00:14:14,310 --> 00:14:16,170
I'll take the punishment quietly.

187
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:18,400
But I'm not making fun of you.

188
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:25,210
As long as my boss accepts you as a customer, she probably won't report you.

189
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:30,050
A-Are you sure?

190
00:14:31,870 --> 00:14:36,990
But aren't you a student? What are you doing here at this time?

191
00:14:38,090 --> 00:14:40,060
Yes, I'm a student.

192
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:43,160
As for school... I'm worried about it.

193
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:45,530
I don't have an answer either.

194
00:14:45,530 --> 00:14:49,890
Honestly, I'm thinking about quitting.

195
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,150
It is indeed hard to go to school.

196
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:58,600
The teachers are crappy and so are the students.

197
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:02,950
But the most worthless of all

198
00:15:02,950 --> 00:15:08,620
It's me. I can't change anything about myself.

199
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:14,130
But that's not you.

200
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:17,830
The courage to take responsibility for your own future

201
00:15:17,830 --> 00:15:23,500
and the determination to put it into practice. I think this is important.

202
00:15:24,990 --> 00:15:27,790
Wow, that speech was really good.

203
00:15:27,790 --> 00:15:31,830
I was just pretending to be an old man.

204
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:36,020
But I'm just a loser.

205
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:38,460
A loser in this damn society.

206
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:41,060
Not at all. That's not true.

207
00:15:41,060 --> 00:15:46,390
Because you're here at our restaurant, I'm sure your wish will come true.

208
00:16:04,450 --> 00:16:08,260
Why does it have so many ingredients?

209
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,730
It's done. Put it back in its place.

210
00:16:26,450 --> 00:16:28,970
You should be more careful.

211
00:16:28,970 --> 00:16:33,260
Oh, I've been having a bit of a headache since earlier.

212
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:40,820
But what do you want in return for the wish?

213
00:16:40,820 --> 00:16:44,230
- An arm? 
 - What? What did you just say?

214
00:16:44,230 --> 00:16:47,300
- An... An arm? 
 - Yeah.

215
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:49,250
An arm.

216
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:52,930
You shouldn't say that so easily. You told me before,

217
00:16:52,930 --> 00:16:56,250
"Thoughts and words have power, so there's no turning back."

218
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:58,690
But I'm not saying this easily.

219
00:16:58,690 --> 00:17:02,700
I mean... what makes this wish so difficult and great?

220
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:05,490
He just wants a job and a normal life like everyone else—

221
00:17:05,490 --> 00:17:10,520
Your life or your arm. Which one would you choose?

222
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:17,130
Your arm is stuck between the rocks of despair. There's no one to save you.

223
00:17:17,130 --> 00:17:22,350
You have to cut off one arm to live. So what are you going to do?

224
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:30,720
Even so, you're the one making that decision right now.

225
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:33,190
Not the person with their arm stuck.

226
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:36,490
He's someone who has been working hard this whole time.

227
00:17:36,490 --> 00:17:40,360
It could have a lifelong impact on his successful employment

228
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:43,520
and his future career.

229
00:17:53,890 --> 00:17:56,290
It's silky chicken soup.

230
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:59,360
If you eat this, your wish will come true.

231
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:03,160
But it isn't for free.

232
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:10,360
As you know, I am dirt poor, so I have nothing.

233
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:12,160
Use your body to pay.

234
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:15,420
B-By my body, you mean...?

235
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:20,100
Just two of those will do.

236
00:18:22,620 --> 00:18:25,850
These two?

237
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:31,760
- If you don't like the offer, then don't eat. 
 - Oh, no. Wait a moment.

238
00:18:35,260 --> 00:18:39,150
 Studying while working hard, stacking up specs, what's the point?

239
00:18:39,150 --> 00:18:40,590
 The starting point is different.

240
00:18:40,590 --> 00:18:43,590
 Your mother was so worthless. That's why you're having a hard time.

241
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:45,060
 I am sorry.

242
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:47,030
 How can you talk like that?

243
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:49,760
 You work hard all the time because of me.

244
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:52,630
 I'll get a job soon so don't worry.

245
00:18:52,630 --> 00:18:57,060
 What will you do if you get sicker? Don't you need surgery?

246
00:18:57,060 --> 00:19:01,330
I only have to give... two fingers, right?

247
00:19:04,260 --> 00:19:08,250
